      "text": [
        " رِوَايَةِ اَلسَّكُونِيِّ قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ : \"لاَ قَطْعَ فِي ثَمَرٍ وَ لاَ كَثَرٍ وَ اَلْكَثَرُ هُوَ اَلْجُمَّارُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5107 - In the narration of Al-Sakuni, the Messenger of Allah (swt) (peace be upon him and his family) said: \"There is no cutting (of the hand) for stealing fruit or kathar.\"\nAnd kathar refers to the inner core of palm trees (Al-jummar)."
        ]
      }
    },
